# Keep the build context small AND keep local env/secrets out of image layers.
# Runtime env is injected by the orchestrator (--env-file on the VPS), never baked.
**/node_modules
**/dist
**/.next
**/out
**/coverage
**/.turbo

# never copy local env files into the image (e.g. apps/backend/.env.production).
# NOTE: no `!...` negation anywhere in this file — a re-include pattern forces
# BuildKit to walk every dir (incl. node_modules) and can fail on Windows pnpm
# junctions. .env.example lives in the repo for docs; it isn't needed in-image.
**/.env
**/.env.*

# frontend deploys on Vercel. We don't exclude it wholesale here because the
# Dockerfile needs apps/frontend/package.json for --frozen-lockfile validation
# (a dir-exclude + `!` re-include negation can trip the Windows junction walk).
# Frontend SOURCE never enters the image — the Dockerfile only COPYs the
# backend, shared, and the individual manifests. node_modules/.next are excluded
# above, so the extra context is just a few MB of source.

# git + tooling + docs that don't belong in the image
.git
.gitignore
.github
.kamal
infra
**/*.log
**/.DS_Store
.vscode
.idea
**/*.tsbuildinfo
README.md
CLAUDE.md
